  "original_title": "\u0b9a\u0bc0\u0ba9 \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0b9e\u0bcd\u0b9e\u0bbe\u0ba9 \u0b86\u0baf\u0bcd\u0bb5\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd \u0b95\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bc1\u0bb1\u0bbf\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0b95\u0b9f\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0baa\u0b9f\u0bc8\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0b85\u0bb1\u0bbf\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0b9f\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd\u0bb2\u0bc8 -\u00a0\u0b95\u0b9f\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0baa\u0b9f\u0bc8",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Navy not notified of Chinese scientific research vessel - Navy",
      "author": "T Yuwaraj",
      "body_lines": [
        "Navy Spokesperson Captain Indika de Silva told Weerakesari that the Navy has not been informed about the Chinese scientific research vessel Yuan Wang 5, which is reported to be arriving at Ambantota Port, and that he does not know enough about it.",
        "The arrival of the said Chinese ship has now sparked a new controversy in the country. It has been reported that the said Chinese ship will arrive at Ambantota port on the 11th and will be anchored there until the 17th. India announced that it had prior knowledge of the ship's arrival in Sri Lanka.",
        "India, which has expressed strong opposition to this, has requested the government to provide a complete clarification regarding the reason for the arrival of the said ship and its activities during the period when it was anchored at Ambantota port.",
        "The high level of Delhi has sent a message to Colombo that the arrival of this ship has a direct impact on India's national security issues. After India expressed displeasure about the Chinese ship, China said it hoped that the relevant parties would refrain from interfering with its legitimate maritime activities.",
        "When asked whether any information has been provided to the navy about the Chinese ship which has caused controversy, the navy spokesperson replied as above. I believe that permission for the arrival of this ship will be obtained from the Ministry of Foreign Affairs, Ministry of Defense and Sri Lankan Ports Authority.",
        "However, I don't know any official information about it. Tomorrow morning (this morning) we can gather information about the arrival of this ship and whether there is any connection with the Sri Lanka Navy and provide it.' Navy spokesperson Captain Indika de Silva further informed Weerakesari"
      ],
